Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Sear roast in hot oil until browned completely, about 2 minutes per side. Spread potatoes into the bottom of the slow cooker. Layer baby carrots atop the potatoes and green beans atop the carrots. Place the roast atop the layers of vegetables. Mix cream of mushroom soup, water, and dry onion soup mix together in a bowl; pour over the roast and vegetables. Cook on Low 8 to 10 hours.